    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Straus</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 22, 1888</date>.
                            (Received January 7, 1889.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 151.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the Bible
                        House has for several months past been seeking permission from the minister
                        of public instruction to print in Turkish thirty-live thousand Bible tracts,
                        consisting of the Psalms the Proverbs, the four Gospels, and the Acts.</p>
                <p>The minister of public instruction having declined to give the authorization,
                        the matter was referred to the legation by the Bible House.</p>
                <p>Yesterday I succeeded in having the grand vizier give orders for the
                        necessary authorization.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O. S. Straus.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
